<doc id="1052859" wikidata="Q7821132" url="?curid=1052859" title="Tongoenabiagus">
<text>Tongoenabiagus was the god of the &quot;Fonte do Ídolo&quot; (Portuguese for &quot;Fountain of the Idol&quot;), a 1st-century shrine in Braga (the Roman &quot;Bracara Augusta&quot;) with an inscribed fountain dedicated both to &quot;Tongoenabiagus&quot; and the goddess &quot;Nabia&quot;. His name may derive from the Celtic root &quot;*tenge(o)-&quot; (Old Irish &quot;tongu&quot; &quot;I swear&quot;) and so he may have been associated with the swearing of oaths.

==See also==
*Castro culture
*Pre-Roman peoples of the Iberian Peninsula

